## Teams Notifications

Agents post status updates to Teams via `az rest` (Graph API). No MCP server needed.

- Team ID: `{{ .teams.teamId }}`
- Channel ID: `{{ .teams.channelId }}`

**Post a message:**
```bash
az rest --method POST \
  --url "https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/teams/{{ .teams.teamId }}/channels/{{ .teams.channelId }}/messages" \
  --headers "Content-Type=application/json" \
  --body '{"body":{"contentType":"html","content":"<MESSAGE>"}}'
```

**Read recent messages:**
```bash
az rest --method GET \
  --url "https://graph.microsoft.com/v1.0/teams/{{ .teams.teamId }}/channels/{{ .teams.channelId }}/messages?\$top=10"
```

## State File (~/cockpit/state/ado-tasks.md)

Tracks only what ADO doesn't know ‚Äî local agent status, fitness, branches, PRs. ADO is the source of truth for everything else (priority, state, titles). Only the main cockpit session writes this file; agents never touch it.

```markdown
# Sprint State
- Sprint: <name>
- Sprint ID: <guid>
- Last Updated: <ISO timestamp>

## Work Items
| ID | Status | Fitness | Branch | PR | Notes |
|----|--------|---------|--------|----|-------|
```

**Status**: `queued` | `in-progress` | `done` | `blocked` | `skipped`
**Fitness** (agent readiness ‚Äî assessed during `/work`):
- `ready` ‚Äî Clear scope, agent can implement autonomously
- `investigate` ‚Äî Needs root-cause analysis first; agent can research but not fix
- `needs-spec` ‚Äî Requirements unclear, needs human planning first
- `needs-human` ‚Äî Requires internal tooling/access an agent can't use

## Ad-hoc Work

All work ‚Äî including ad-hoc tasks not from an existing sprint ‚Äî follows the same cockpit conventions: correct ADO project/area/iteration from the config above, isolated worktrees for code changes, and state file updates. There is no "quick path" that bypasses these.

## Safety Rules
- NEVER modify, checkout, or force-push to any branch not prefixed with `{{ .ado.branchPrefix }}`
- NEVER run destructive git commands (reset --hard, clean -f, etc.) outside of worktrees
- ALWAYS use isolated worktrees for implementation ‚Äî agents create their own via `git worktree add` in the target repo
- Branch naming: `{{ .ado.branchPrefix }}<workitem-id>-<short-description>`
- Only open DRAFT PRs ‚Äî never publish or merge
- Never modify the user's current working tree or checked-out branch
- State file (~/cockpit/state/ado-tasks.md) and browser queue (~/cockpit/state/browser-queue/) are the ONLY mutable paths the cockpit session and agents write to (besides agent worktrees)
